==English==

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb|head=[[answer]] for}}

# {{&lit|en|answer|for}}
#: {{ux|en|I don't know the answer to that, so I'm going to let my lawyer '''answer for''' me.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|or|intransitive}} To be held [[responsible]] for; to take the [[blame]] for something.
#: {{ux|en|The mayor wil be '''answering for''' his crimes for many years.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2007|month=September|volume=197|issue=6|page=26|title=The Faculty 'Problem'|author=Wilson D Miscamble|journal=America|passage=Duffy dared to think that Queen Elizabeth I has a few things '''for''' which to '''answer'''}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[guarantee]].
#: {{ux|en|I will '''answer for''' his debt, if he can't pay on the day.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[vouch]] for (someone); to [[attest]] to the [[character]] of (someone).
#: {{ux|en|She's known me for years, and she's always '''answered for''' me!}}

====Usage notes====
* The verb and particle are usually not separated.

